Vintage-style illustration of a weathered leather travel satchel resting on an antique wooden desk, surrounded by scattered maps of Australia and New Zealand with small red pins marking major cities. A steaming cup of coffee sits nearby, and warm afternoon light streams through a window casting long shadows. Faded postcards featuring the Sydney Opera House and New Zealand mountains peek out from the bag's pocket. The color palette is warm sepia tones with touches of deep red and ocean blue, evoking the romance of educational journeys across the Pacific. The composition suggests anticipation and adventure, with the maps slightly curled at the edges showing signs of planning and use.
